An unhandled throw in a route will hit Express's default handler, which can leak stack traces in development mode and won't be logged in structured form in production.

```js
// Must be registered LAST, after all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log with a request-correlatable logger (pino/winston), not console
  req.log?.error({ err }, 'unhandled error');
  const status = err.status || 500;
  res.status(status).json({
    error: status === 500 ? 'internal error' : err.message,
