| Category | Status in current `app.js` |
|---|---|
| A01 Broken Access Control | ❌ `/users` unauthenticated, returns PII |
| A02 Cryptographic Failures | ⚠️ Cleartext HTTP; no TLS guidance |
| A03 Injection | ✅ No user input accepted; no risk today |
| A04 Insecure Design | ⚠️ No rate limits or abuse controls |
| A05 Security Misconfig | ❌ No Helmet; `x-powered-by` leaks; hardcoded config |
| A06 Vulnerable Components | ⚠️ Cannot assess — no `package.json` reviewed; run `npm audit` |
| A07 Identification & AuthN Failures | ❌ No auth layer |
| A08 Software & Data Integrity | N/A |
| A09 Security Logging & Monitoring | ❌ Only `console.log` on startup |
| A10 SSRF | ✅ No outbound HTTP in current code |

---

## Suggested Next Steps

1. Apply the hardened template above.
2. Run `npm audit --production` and `npm outdated` on the project to address A06.
3. Add a linter rule set like `eslint-plugin-security` to catch future regressions.
4. Add tests for the auth middleware (401 without token, 403 with wrong role, 200 with correct role).
5. If this API will ever accept user input, adopt the `zod`-based validator pattern in finding #10 from the first route onward.

