```js
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    ...
  ]);
});
```

**Fix:** Require auth and strip fields that don't need to be public.

```js
app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  const users = getUsers().map(({ id, name }) => ({ id, name })); // no email
  res.json(users);
});
```

---

### 2. **No security headers** (Medium — OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration)
Express ships with no hardening headers by default. Missing `Content-Security-Policy`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-Frame-Options`, etc.

**Fix:** Add [`helmet`](https://helmetjs.github.io/):

```js
