| # | Finding | Severity | OWASP |
|---|---------|----------|-------|
| 1 | No security headers (Helmet missing) | Medium | A05: Security Misconfiguration |
| 2 | PII (email) returned without authentication/authorization | Medium | A01: Broken Access Control / A02: Crypto Failures (data exposure) |
| 3 | No rate limiting | Medium | A04: Insecure Design |
| 4 | No CORS policy configured | Low–Medium | A05 |
| 5 | No structured logging / error handling middleware | Low | A09: Logging & Monitoring Failures |
| 6 | Hard-coded port, no `0.0.0.0`/env binding control | Low | A05 |
| 7 | `x-powered-by: Express` header leaks framework | Low | A05 |
| 8 | No HTTPS/TLS termination guidance | Low | A02 |

**Not present (good):** No SQL/NoSQL queries, no `eval`, no `child_process`, no user-controlled input parsed, no auth tokens, no file system access — so classic injection, SSRF, path traversal, and deserialization risks are currently **N/A**. That said, the app is a scaffold; the moment real inputs are added, most of these become live concerns.

---

