## Scope note

The file is only 22 lines and contains two endpoints returning static data. There are **no database queries, no user input handling, no auth code, and no file/OS operations** in the current source, so classic injection vectors (SQLi, command injection, path traversal, SSRF) are not directly reachable today. Most findings below are about **missing defenses** that should be in place before this grows.

