### 4. No CORS policy declared (OWASP A05)

With no `cors` middleware, browser behavior is the default (same-origin). That's actually safe-by-default, but once you add one it's easy to misconfigure. When you do add it, be explicit:

```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://your-frontend.example.com'], credentials: true }));
```

Avoid `cors({ origin: '*' })` on any endpoint that will eventually take credentials.

### 5. Listens on all interfaces with no TLS (OWASP A02)

`app.listen(3000, ...)` binds `0.0.0.0`. That's fine behind a reverse proxy, but in deployment ensure TLS terminates in front and that the port isn't exposed publicly in raw HTTP.

```js
