const host = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1'; // bind loopback; reverse proxy forwards
app.listen(port, host, () => console.log(`Server on ${host}:${port}`));
```

### 6. No structured error handler (OWASP A09: Security Logging & Monitoring Failures)

An uncaught error will send Express's default HTML stack trace to the client in development mode, which leaks paths and versions. Add a terminal error handler and disable verbose errors outside dev:

```js
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  req.log?.error({ err }, 'request failed'); // structured logging
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' });
});
```

### 7. No body parser limits configured (future-proofing A04)

You don't currently parse bodies, but when you add `express.json()` set a limit to prevent memory-exhaustion DoS:

```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '100kb' }));
```

### 8. `x-powered-by: Express` header leaks stack info

Minor fingerprinting. `helmet()` disables it; if you don't use helmet, call `app.disable('x-powered-by')`.

